FBIS4-50409 "drchi096_p_94001" FBIS-CHI-94-096 Daily Report 14 May 1994 Central-South Region Guangdong Military District Commander on Militia Building Guangdong Military District Commander on Militia Building HK1805003394 Guangzhou Guangdong People's Radio Network in Mandarin 0400 GMT 14 May 94 HK1805003394 Guangzhou Guangdong People's Radio Network Mandarin BFN [Text] Wen Yuzhu, member of the Standing Committee of the Guangdong Provincial CPC Committee and commander of the Guangdong Provincial Military District, put forward the general demand on the building of the militia emergency detachments of the whole province for some time to come at the provincial on-the-spot meeting on the building of the militia emergency detachments, which ended in Huizhou yesterday. He said it is necessary to build the militia emergency detachments of our province into a politically reliable, well-equipped, and well-trained contingent with sound organization, with the required number of militiamen, and with good supply. In case of emergency, the detachments really should be able to assemble at the first call, to be ready for combat, to take orders, to play their role, and to make contributions to state security, social stability, and economic development. The meeting disclosed that at present, the militia emergency detachments of our province have a total of 116 companies and 535 independent emergency platoons. Their organization is sound and their education, training, and management are quite strict and regular. At the meeting, the provincial military district commended 33 advanced companies and platoons and 52 advanced militiamen.
